## Operators

### Arithmetic

Arithmetic operators are simple functions that perform an operation on two numbers.

```javascript
var addition = (x, y) => x + y;
var subtraction = (x, y) => x - y;
var multiplication = (x, y) => x * y;
var division = (x, y) => x / y;
var modulo = (x, y) => x % y;
var moddiv = (x, y) => modulo(division(x, y), y);

console.log(addition(1, 2));
// 3

console.log(subtraction(1, 2));
// -1

console.log(multiplication(1, 2));
// 2

console.log(division(4, 2));
// 2.0

console.log(modulo(4, 2));
// 1

console.log(moddiv(4, 2));
// [1.0, 0.5]
```

### Bitwise Operators

Bitwise operators perform an operation on two numbers using a bitwise operation.

